Former Rangers striker Ally McCoist expressed his delight at the early return of Joe Aribo from the Africa Cup of Nations after defeat to Tunisia. Aribo’s Nigeria side were knocked out of the competition thanks to a Youssef Msakni goal but that does mean that the 25-year-old is available for selection earlier than expected. McCoist admitted to supporting Tunisia over Aribo’s Nigeria on BT Sport’s Scottish Football Extra on Tuesday as he hoped the Light Blues star could return as soon as possible.   Watford unveils Samuel Kalu     Eagles ‘ll bounce back after AFCON disappointment, says Musa     Mouktar wants Qatar 2022 Task Force for Eagles   McCoist refers to wearing an Algeria scarf but we can only assume he has got mistaken between them and Tunisia. “I’ve got to be brutally honest here, I sat and watched with my Algeria scarf on and I cannot lie to you, as disappointed as I was for Nigeria and Joe, I got over it very quickly,” said McCoist. - Advertisement - “He’s absolutely vital. He’s probably been one of the best players in the league so far this year. “I think it would be very important for Rangers’ chances of retaining the title to have a fit and healthy Joe Aribo arrive safely back on these shores.”